But cannot get the directory from which my file is 'double-clicked' using "GetCurrentDirName". 
If set CLI as ToolType, GetCurrentDirName works, but then get bogus data as filename. As your program is launched by Workbench, it doesn't have a CLI structure indeed, hence why GetCurrentDirName() doesn't work without CLI tooltype. But you should be able to use NameFromLock() and find what you need from there. 

